<DOC><DOCNO> AP880503-0105 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-03-88 1239EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--FlagArrests     05-03 0147</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Flag Arrests,0151</SECOND><HEAD>Five Arrested for Damaging or Stealing Flags</HEAD><DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Five people were arrested fordamaging or stealing Soviet and Czechoslovak flags decoratingstreets for May Day rallies, newspapers reported Tuesday.   In Bratislava, three people were arrested Saturday for pullingdown Soviet flags, the party daily Rude Pravo said.   A Prague student was detained Sunday for intentionally damaginga Czechoslovak flag near the Letna grounds, Prague's center for theMay Day rally, it said.   The youth daily Mlada Fronta said police Sunday arrested a22-year-old manager of a restaurant for stealing three red flagsfrom the May Day decorations in Prague's tenth district.   None of those arrested was identified.   Rude Pravo also reported the arrest of an 18-year-old youth inTrnava, Slovakia, who painted swastikas on a building wherecitizens were meeting. It said the man would be prosecuted forpropagating fascism.</TEXT></DOC>